Bishop to queen four, level two.

236
00:12:56,879 --> 00:13:00,554
-Check.
-Sheldon, Knight takes Bishop.

237
00:13:01,519 --> 00:13:02,508
You all right?

238
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:04,838
I'm fine.

239
00:13:05,719 --> 00:13:08,870
Are you? You left your queen exposed
from above...

240
00:13:09,040 --> 00:13:12,237
...trapped your knight in the corner,
and you keep sighing and saying:

241
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:13,799
"Why me?"

242
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:15,429
[SIGHS]

243
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:16,919
Very well.

244
00:13:17,079 --> 00:13:20,708
Can I ask you a question
about women?

245
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:24,871
We got you that book last year.
Wasn't everything in there?

246
00:13:25,040 --> 00:13:28,555
No. I'm having
a relationship problem with Amy.

247
00:13:29,719 --> 00:13:31,789
And by the way,
that book gave me nightmares.

248
00:13:33,079 --> 00:13:34,671
If it makes you feel any better...

249
00:13:34,839 --> 00:13:37,069
...I screwed things up pretty good
with Penny.

250
00:13:37,759 --> 00:13:39,590
Look at us, Leonard.

251
00:13:39,759 --> 00:13:44,230
Engaging in the social convention of
men bellyaching about their old ladies.

252
00:13:44,759 --> 00:13:47,478
I guess we are. So....

253
00:13:47,639 --> 00:13:49,038
What's going on?

254
00:13:49,199 --> 00:13:52,669
Believe it or not,
Amy has embarked on a campaign...

255
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:57,550
...to increase my feelings for her
by making me happy.

256
00:13:59,639 --> 00:14:02,437
I'm sorry,
that must be very difficult for you.

257
00:14:03,120 --> 00:14:05,236
It's awful. This morning...

258
00:14:05,399 --> 00:14:08,755
...she arranged for me to be
an Amtrak Junior Conductor for the day.

259
00:14:08,920 --> 00:14:13,516
It's usually only open to children.
She got them to make an exception.

260
00:14:14,160 --> 00:14:16,276
Shame on her.

261
00:14:16,999 --> 00:14:19,069
They let me blow the whistle,
Leonard.

262
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:22,031
She's good.

263
00:14:22,199 --> 00:14:24,508
I know. And it gets worse.

264
00:14:24,680 --> 00:14:28,434
Her efforts are causing me
to have affectionate feelings for her...

265
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:31,478
...at inappropriate times.

266
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:36,278
You mean like in bed
or in the shower?

267
00:14:36,439 --> 00:14:40,512
No. And would you please stop
referencing that infernal book?

268
00:14:41,959 --> 00:14:43,597
For example, this morning...

269
00:14:43,759 --> 00:14:47,638
...l was calculating the random motion
of virtual particles in a vacuum...

270
00:14:47,799 --> 00:14:54,272
...when suddenly, the particles morphed
into an image of Amy's dandruff...

271
00:14:57,079 --> 00:15:02,028
...gently cascading down onto her pale,
slightly hunched shoulders.

272
00:15:02,240 --> 00:15:03,559
[SHELDON GROANS]

273
00:15:03,719 --> 00:15:06,517
What has that vixen done to me,
Leonard?

274
00:15:06,680 --> 00:15:08,238
How do I make it stop?

275
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:12,110
Well, if you had a physical relationship,
I'd say propose during sex.

276
00:15:12,280 --> 00:15:14,840
Turns out that's a real mood-killer.

277
00:15:15,680 --> 00:15:18,035
-I assume we're talking about you now?
-Yeah.

278
00:15:18,199 --> 00:15:21,396
So that's how this works?
I complain and then you complain...

279
00:15:21,560 --> 00:15:23,949
...and no one offers any solutions?

280
00:15:25,040 --> 00:15:26,758
Pretty much.

281
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:29,589
Well, no wonder the women
are winning.

282
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:35,550
Mr. Rostenkowski, are you busy?

283
00:15:35,719 --> 00:15:38,108
Just looking at some old pictures.
Come on in.

284
00:15:38,279 --> 00:15:42,352
Family pictures, or--?
Holy crap, that's a dead person.

285
00:15:42,959 --> 00:15:45,678
Last murder case before I retired.

286
00:15:45,839 --> 00:15:47,750
How many bodies do you see there?

287
00:15:47,920 --> 00:15:51,071
Careful. It's a trick question.

288
00:15:51,240 --> 00:15:57,156
-l'm not sure.
-No, you'll never get it. It's a fraction.

289
00:15:58,519 --> 00:15:59,554
How about that, heh.

290
00:15:59,719 --> 00:16:03,792
Anyway, sir,
I need to talk to you about something.

291
00:16:03,959 --> 00:16:05,358
Walnut?

292
00:16:06,280 --> 00:16:08,271
No, thank you. I'm allergic.

293
00:16:08,480 --> 00:16:13,554
Oh, sure. My partner used to have that.
He's dead now.

294
00:16:15,160 --> 00:16:18,118
-From nuts, heh?
-No, his wife shot him.

295
00:16:19,319 --> 00:16:22,675
But she was nuts. So in a way....

296
00:16:23,919 --> 00:16:26,672
Nice story. Anyway...

297
00:16:26,839 --> 00:16:28,989
...the reason
I wanted to talk to you is...

298
00:16:29,160 --> 00:16:33,711
...NASA has moved up my launch
to the International Space Station.

299
00:16:33,920 --> 00:16:37,629
-Yeah, so?
-So the date is going to conflict...

300
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:41,156
...with me marrying your daughter.
Now, I know what you're going to say.

301
00:16:41,319 --> 00:16:43,787
I made a commitment to Bernadette
and to your family...

302
00:16:43,999 --> 00:16:47,628
...and I've got a lot of nerve coming here
and demanding that we postpone this.

303
00:16:47,839 --> 00:16:50,911
Well, message heard and understood.
Mission cancelled. Thank you.

304
00:16:52,680 --> 00:16:54,033
Where are you going?

305
00:16:54,199 --> 00:16:55,393
I'm sorry.

306
00:16:55,560 --> 00:16:57,710
May I be excused?

307
00:16:57,879 --> 00:17:00,552
No, you may not.
Let me tell you something.

308
00:17:00,719 --> 00:17:03,677
When I first met you....
You just gonna stand there?

309
00:17:05,160 --> 00:17:07,310
I'm sorry, I didn't know.
Is this going to...?

310
00:17:07,520 --> 00:17:09,954
Well, I should sit--
May I be seated? I'll just sit.

311
00:17:12,679 --> 00:17:15,796
When I first met you, I didn't like you.

312
00:17:17,159 --> 00:17:19,150
I'm aware of that, sir.

313
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:21,995
But then you and I
had some time together.

314
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:23,633
Uh-huh, heh.

315
00:17:23,799 --> 00:17:25,790
It did not get better.

316
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:28,069
Right, right, heh.

317
00:17:28,240 --> 00:17:30,037
That silly Beatle haircut.

318
00:17:31,440 --> 00:17:33,237
You riding around on a red Vespa.

319
00:17:33,400 --> 00:17:35,960
And you're still living at home
with your mother.

320
00:17:36,559 --> 00:17:40,393
To be honest, I thought Bernadette
chose you to punish me.

321
00:17:42,279 --> 00:17:44,588
But then I heard
about your astronaut thing...

322
00:17:44,759 --> 00:17:48,434
...and I realized ljudged you too fast.

323
00:17:48,599 --> 00:17:51,636
Maybe you are the right guy
for my little girl.

324
00:17:51,799 --> 00:17:55,155
Oh, I am. And just so you know
I'd still be an astronaut...

325
00:17:55,320 --> 00:17:56,753
...even if I didn't go to space, heh.

326
00:17:56,960 --> 00:18:00,748
You know, I've got an ID card
and a NASA golf shirt.

327
00:18:00,919 --> 00:18:01,954
No, no. You gotta go.

328
00:18:02,120 --> 00:18:04,270
You can't turn down
an opportunity like this.

329
00:18:04,440 --> 00:18:05,429
[STAMMERS]

330
00:18:05,599 --> 00:18:06,634
But what about the wedding...

331
00:18:06,799 --> 00:18:09,188
...and all the money you put down
for the reception?

332
00:18:09,360 --> 00:18:10,839
You let me worry about that.

333
00:18:10,999 --> 00:18:14,674
You go up to that space station
and you make me proud.

334
00:18:19,159 --> 00:18:20,228
Um, okay.

335
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:21,389
[CHUCKLES]

336
00:18:21,559 --> 00:18:23,117
You got a problem with that?

337
00:18:23,719 --> 00:18:25,630
All right, look,
I'm gonna level with you.

338
00:18:25,799 --> 00:18:28,916
I'm terrified about going into space.

339
00:18:29,080 --> 00:18:32,117
I mean, uh,
what ifl don't make it back?

340
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:34,989
It's gonna be okay, son.

341
00:18:36,760 --> 00:18:39,911
-You really think so?
-Of course.

342
00:18:40,079 --> 00:18:44,550
A pretty girl like Bernadette.
She'll find a new guy.

343
00:18:52,799 --> 00:18:54,994
-Hey.
-Hey.

344
00:18:55,159 --> 00:18:56,956
-Off to work?
-Yeah.

345
00:18:57,120 --> 00:18:59,680
-Have a nice night.
-Okay, you too.

346
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:02,750
Penny, just wait.

347
00:19:03,159 --> 00:19:05,878
I've been thinking about what I said
when we were in bed.

348
00:19:06,039 --> 00:19:07,916
Yeah, I've been thinking about it too.

349
00:19:08,519 --> 00:19:10,077
I noticed you never answered me.

350
00:19:11,799 --> 00:19:13,391
You're right.

351
00:19:18,479 --> 00:19:19,468


352
00:19:22,520 --> 00:19:25,080
-Uh, follow-up. Are we still dating?
PENNY: Yep.

353
00:19:25,239 --> 00:19:28,549
-ls it still weird because I proposed?
PENNY: Yep.

354
00:19:28,760 --> 00:19:30,398
l have a couple more
quick questions.

355
00:19:30,560 --> 00:19:33,393
-Do you wanna call me from the car?
PENNY: Nope.

356
00:19:35,319 --> 00:19:37,674
I played that pretty well.

357
00:19:38,679 --> 00:19:40,635
[MEDICAL TRICORDER BEEPING]

358
00:19:49,680 --> 00:19:51,557
Hello, Leonard.

359
00:19:51,720 --> 00:19:54,757
-What are you doing?
-We're playing doctor.

360
00:19:56,119 --> 00:19:58,189
Star Trek style.

361
00:19:59,640 --> 00:20:01,870
I'm in hell, Leonard.

362
00:20:03,839 --> 00:20:05,511
Don't stop.

363
00:20:06,719 --> 00:20:08,914
[MEDICAL TRICORDER BEEPING]

364
00:20:32,919 --> 00:20:34,910
[English - us - an]

